comments.body:
@SteveL-MSFT: Thanks for the clarification re table view.

We now know that the behavior is by design, but perhaps it's time to revisit that, as @thezim suggests - especially given that it is behavior related to _for-display-only_ output that no one can expect to rely on for long-term stability and machine parsing, as [@lzybkr  has previously noted](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/4767#issuecomment-328904091).

Doing away with the padding might also help with #4767 and the [fix that @lzybkr had contemplated](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/4767#issuecomment-329243332).
